author: Brianne Tolj For Daily Mail Australia
title: 'Lotto rat' who kept millions forced to pay out co-workers | Daily Mail Online
text: 'Lotto rat' who kept a $16.6MILLION winning lottery ticket he won with colleagues before quitting his job agrees to pay former co-workers Gary Baron, 50, has reached a settlement with 14 of his former colleagues The Victorian truck driver won a $16.6 million Powerball lotto in 2014 Baron bought properties, a BMW convertible and quit his job after winning His colleagues claim he bought the ticket with their lotto syndicate funds Settlement will be finalised tomorrow but it is unknown how much they will get Published: 10:33 GMT, 1 February 2017 | Updated: 14:16 GMT, 1 February 2017 239 shares
